modules.description: Provides functions to normalize Unicode strings according to Unicode standards, including decomposition, composition, and case folding. Works with OCaml strings and Unicode code points. Used to standardize text input for consistent processing in internationalized applications.

Processes Unicode text normalization using specified forms, handling incremental input and output through stateful operations. Works with Unicode characters and arrays representing decomposition data, supporting canonical and compatibility normalization. Used to normalize text streams or partial input sequences in real-time applications.

Converts UTF-8, UTF-16BE, and UTF-16LE encoded strings to specified Unicode normalization forms. Accepts strings in any of these encodings and returns them in NFC, NFD, NFKC, or NFKD form. Used to standardize text input for consistent processing in applications handling multilingual data.
